# Trivy allowlist — every entry MUST justify itself.
#
# Format:
#   # <CVE-id>: one-line justification (severity, base image, why deferred)
#   # Re-check by: YYYY-MM-DD
#   <CVE-id>
#
# Rules:
# - Only allowlist a CVE when (a) no fixed version is available yet, or
#   (b) the vulnerable code path is unreachable from our application.
# - Always include a "Re-check by" date no more than 60 days out. The
#   weekly Trivy schedule will re-fail once a fix lands.
# - Never allowlist CRITICAL secret-disclosure or RCE vulns without
#   explicit reviewer sign-off in the PR description.
#
# Keep this file empty when nothing needs to be deferred — that's the
# desired steady state.
